The paper deals with kernel-based filters that are commonly used in image processing, which suggests that it belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of efficient algorithms for spatial convolutions, which could fall under machine learning (cs.MM) and/or learning theory (cs.LG). The use of the Nyström method for approximating the eigendecomposition of large matrices suggests that it could also belong to the information theory (cs.IT) and numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories.
